ors of power. Beginning with promises to eliminate hunger and ending with food shortages and burning supermarkets, Jennifer Adair provides an in-depth account of the Alfonsín government's unfulfilled projects to ensure basic needs against the backdrop of a looming neoliberal world order. As it moves from the presidential palace to the streets, this original book offers a compelling reinterpretation of post-dictatorship Argentina and Latin America's so-called lost decade.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh  aalfonsin governments unfulfilled projects.  aargentina.  aargentinas transition to democracy.  acompelling.  aeveryday meanings of rights.  afood shortages and burning supermarkets.  alatin americas lost decade.  alived experience of democratic return.  aneoliberal world order.  aoriginal.  apresidential palace to streets.  apromises to eliminate hunger.  areinterpretation of post dictatorship argentina.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520973282zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520973282423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520973282.jpg  a978-3-11-066763-9  UC Press eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Histo